<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 5000i, 9100i, 9200i, 9400i, 9900i MODELS - Starting 03/01/1999 - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - BLOWER MOTOR ASSEMBLY - SLEEPER COMPARTMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x1602316" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BLOWER MOTOR ASSEMBLY - SLEEPER COMPARTMENT</title>
        <svcsubproc id="x1602318">
            <title>Remove</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602350">Figure 42</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1602350" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602342.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Blower Motor Assembly (Sleeper Compartment)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the key switch and blower motor switches are in the OFF position.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove seat belt restraining bracket from passenger side trim panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove screws from lower passenger side trim panel to gain access to the sleeper
                    compartment blower.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the section of air duct that connects the blend-air unit to the blower motor
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connectors from the blower motor assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the three bolts from the blower motor assembly mounting flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the blower motor assembly and tilt it outward to remove.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="x1602319">
            <title>Install</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602350">Figure 42</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install the duct onto the blower motor assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tilt the blower motor and duct assembly toward the duct enclosure and slide the assembly
                    into position. Make sure the blower motor duct engages the duct in the enclosure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the bolts in the blower motor assembly mounting flange.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the electrical connectors to the blower motor assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the mounting screws for the duct section between the blower motor
                    assembly and the blend air unit.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully position the trim panel around the duct and install the mounting screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the seat belt restraining bracket.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
